            <thetext>A recurring pattern for users is to make an existing JS library available to a qooxdoo app. A good way to achieve this is to wrap the JS library into a qooxdoo lib, like e.g. QxDyGraphs, QxJqPlot or QxProtovis do. It would be good to have a skeleton for this that wraps a minimal (made-up) JS resource with a qooxdoo interface. Boilerplate code would handling loading of the JS resource, and provide a class interface to its functionality.

This skeleton should also have a section in the manual.</thetext>
